participating-org.narrative:
Intermon Oxfam has been working in Morocco since 1993, and it has been working with local organisations in longer-term partnerships. During the coming five years, Intermon Oxfam in Morocco will implement three main programs which correlate with Oxfam Novib's strategies for the country:
- A program on womens rights, focusing on combating violence against women, increase participation of women in decision-making and fostering a culture of female citizenship and equality;
- An Economic Justice program, including income-generating activities, labour rights and corporate social responsibility, as well as trade agreements;
- A citizenship and governance program supporting the rule of law, justice reform and constitutional reform; supporting civil society networks and forums; as well as budget monitoring and accountability in public affairs.
